			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Wow.. Just wow 37 bard<a name="37723"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 3 04 9:52 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Effie, I have to agree totally.  Many many many times people hear from me what I want to do in a group, and then when I show them by what I do, they drop jaw and tongue lag...only good lag in the game.  hehe.
<br />

<br />
I know this is going to get a few feathers ruffled, but we have a misunderstood reptuation as a class because it's OUR FAULT.  Not you and me, but Bards overall.  People understand how bards work, they see us doing what we do, and they remember.  It's not their fault we have so many poor examples out there.  I grouped with a few in LDoN, and they both were just DUDE HOW'D YA DO THAT!!!  I share it, helped them practice it too, and they were stunned that I took an hour to give em a few pointers...that tells me that we aren't as tight a class as we should be.  Share the knowledge, help them with better gear, not uber, but better if possible, but mostly teach them to rely on the songs.
<br />

<br />
I see so many of them go thru the first 30ish levels as singing warriors.  This gets skills maxed by then, 1h 2h, etc...but not their instruments which is where the real power of the bard is found.  I had a challenge to start on a new server, proving to this ...ugh...ranger...that I could level to 20 in less than 12 hours of play.  Hit ding 20 and had my surname in 10 hours and 15 minutes.  No gear.  Nothing but cloth items, and a Orcish Lute of singing and a basic drum.  He was just dumbfounded, or just dumb for being a ranger...lol.  
<br />

<br />
By this time, others that group with them see these weaker melee class players just expending energy and wasting mana on the healers.  When they finally get a taste of a bard who can pull one at a time with no adds, not aggro once (even with a CHOS), and twist up to 5 songs across the mob and group...they just wonder what planet this player is from...cuz they never saw a bard do what I do, and others who know the class well.  Knowing great gear drops helps in plat, better armor is nice, sweet equipment and weaps are awesome...but if they have all this and don't know what song's to line up with at each situation...they're just wasting their time.  May as well get your tradeskills up instead.
<br />

<br />
I was overwhelmed at the opinion of some toward bards, but until I really watched other bard players (especially on my server Saryrn)...oh man.  They look like rangers without Archery skill.  there are a few hidden gems out there, watch for them and ask a ton of questions.  I got myself a bard Sensei (Adamio, you rock bro!!!) and he showed me the true Twist and Shout that puts the bard class above all others.  If you see a bard, ask him if he comes here to read the site, how his twisting is going, and how he's learning the class.  If you are getting kudos on the class, pass on some good tips to lower level bards, so they won't be musical Conan's, which sigh, is very embarrasing.
<br />

<br />
...Arnold in a musical....Twins was bad enough!!!
<br />

<br />
/rant off
<br />

<br />
thanks, 
<br />

<br />
Filo
<br />
  
<br />
</span></td>
